ZH: 这个世界并不是坏的，只是有时候我们看待它的方式不对。
EN: This world is not bad, it's just sometimes we don't look at it the right way.

ZH: 这个孩子并不坏，只是缺乏一点父母的关爱。
EN: This child is not bad, just lacking a bit of parental love.

ZH: 我们不能因为一次失败就觉得自己很坏。
EN: We can't think we are bad just because of one failure.

ZH: 那个人做坏事的时候总是笑嘻嘻的。
EN: That person always smiles when doing bad things.

ZH: 别觉得坏事做的人就是坏人。
EN: Don't think that people who do bad things are bad people.

ZH: 有时候坏事会引起好事。
EN: Sometimes bad things can lead to good things.

ZH: 他们的意图并不坏，只是方法不对。
EN: Their intentions are not bad, just their methods are wrong.

ZH: 别被表面上的坏人蒙蔽了眼睛。
EN: Don't be blinded by the appearance of bad people.

ZH: 这种坏行为是不能被原谅的。
EN: This kind of bad behavior is unforgivable.

ZH: 我们要努力做好事，而不是做坏事。
EN: We should strive to do good things, not bad things.

ZH: 不要因为坏情绪而对别人发泄。
EN: Don't take out bad mood on others.

ZH: 唯一能对抗坏事的方法就是做好事。
EN: The only way to fight bad things is to do good things.

ZH: 不要纵容别人的坏行为。
EN: Don't indulge in other people's bad behavior.

ZH: 必须学会区分好和坏。
EN: You must learn to distinguish between good and bad.

ZH: 坏事发生是无法避免的。
EN: Bad things happen and cannot be avoided.

ZH: 不要因为他的坏言论而向他低头。
EN: Don't bow to him because of his bad remarks.

ZH: 永远不要低估一个人做坏事的可能性。
EN: Never underestimate the possibility of a person doing bad things.

ZH: 不要让坏事情触碰到你的善良。
EN: Don't let bad things touch your kindness.

ZH: 不要因为别人的坏行为而改变自己的原则。
EN: Don't change your principles because of other people's bad behavior.
